The paper deals with Private Information Retrieval (PIR) in models where a database is stored across several servers using coding techniques from distributed storage. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The paper also discusses the design of PIR array codes, which involves the study of the maximum virtual server rate of a PIR array code with the k-PIR property. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the Distributed Systems (cs.DS) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of subspace codes, which suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DC) and Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) categories.
